{{Subspeciesbox | name = Ruwenzori black-and-white colobus | image = Colobus angolensis.jpg | image_caption = | image2 = | image2_caption = | status = VU | status_system = IUCN3.1 | status_ref = <ref name=msw3/> | genus = Colobus | species = angolensis | subspecies = ruwenzori<ref name="Colobus"/> | authority = [[Duke Adolf Friedrich of Mecklenburg|Friedrichs]] }}
The '''ruwenzori colobus''' (''Colobus angolensis ruwenzori'')<ref name="Colobus">{{cite book|title=Rwanda|url=https://books.google.al/books?id=NVTLZ41XyX8C&pg=PA144&dq=Ruwenzori+colobus&hl=sq&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjCnKbspb3eAhXDCewKHXbCA6gQ6AEIIjAA#v=onepage&q=Ruwenzori%20colobus&f=false|author1=Philip Briggs|author2=Janice Booth|ISBN=978-1-84162-306-1}}</ref> or '''Ruwenzori black-and-white colobus''', is a [[primate]] [[subspecies]] of [[Angola colobus]], native to [[Rwanda]] at [[Nyungwe National Park]].<ref name=""pp1>{{Cite web|url=http://nyungwepark.com/nyungwe/the-park/|title=Nyungwe Forest|accessdate=21 April 2013|publisher=Official website of Nyungwe National Park.}}</ref>
==Taxonomy== [[Duke Adolf Friedrich of Mecklenburg|Adolf Friedrichs]] recognized the validity of subspecies as ''Colobus angolensis ruwenzori''.<ref name="Colobus"/><ref name=msw3>{{MSW3 Groves|pages=168|id=12100598}}</ref>
==Characteristics== Like all [[black-and-white colobus]], the ruwenzori colobus has black fur and a black face, surrounded by long, white locks of hair. It also has a mantle of white hair on the shoulders. The long, thin tail can be either black or white, but the tip is always white. There is a significant regional variation in the total amount of white on the body and the length of the fur.{{cn|date=November 2018}}
==Ecology and behavior== The ruwenzori colobus is a highly arboreal and acrobatic leaf-eater.<ref name="Colobus"/> Their diet consists of about two thirds of leaves and one third of fruit and seeds.
Although all ''[[Colobus]]'' [[species]] are very sociable, they usually move on the troops of several hundred [[animal]]s.<ref name="Colobus"/>
==Distribution and habitat== The ruwenzori colobus inhabit [[rainforest]]s of Nyungwe National Park near [[Rwenzori Mountains]].<ref name="Colobus"/> Some reports indicate that the subspecies may occur in some [[Tanzania]]n [[region]]s.<ref name="AndersonCowlishawRowcliffe2007">{{Cite journal|last1=Anderson |first1=J. |last2=Cowlishaw |first2=G. |last3=Rowcliffe |first3=J. M. |doi=10.1007/s10764-007-9143-7 |title=Effects of forest fragmentation on the abundance of ''Colobus angolensis palliatus'' in Kenya's coastal forests |journal=International Journal of Primatology |volume=28 |issue=3 |pages=637 |year=2007 |pmid= |pmc= |url=http://crs.itb.ac.id/media/jurnal/refs/draft/Primates/fulltext(22).pdf }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
